[1] Cholera - Nepal (Banke)
Date: Mon 9 Aug 2010
Source: The Himalayan Times [edited]
<http://www.thehimalayantimes.com/fullNews.php?headline=Killer+cholera+claims+9th+victim&NewsID=252933>


According to the head of the Community Health Office, Dhirjung Shah, a 35
year old man, local resident of Tulsipur and employee of a hotel in
Nepalgunj, died this morning [9 Aug 2010] while undergoing treatment at
Tribhuvan University Teaching Hospital, Nepalgunj. With his death the death
toll has gone up to 8 according to the Community Health Office.

[byline: Surendra Kafle]

