[2] Cholera - Nepal (Banke)
Date: Sun 8 Aug 2010
Source: Nepal News [edited]
<http://www.nepalnews.com/main/index.php/news-archive/2-political/8199-lawmakers-in-banke-to-inspect-cholera-hit-areas-.html>


A team of lawmakers which reached Nepalgunj on Saturday [7 Aug 2010] to
inspect various areas of Banke district affected by cholera started work on
Sunday [8 Aug 2010]. Earlier today, 8 Aug 2010, the house team met the
chief of the District Public Health (DPH) office and inquired about the
latest developments to bring the outbreak under control.

The Constituent Assembly [CA] secretariat on Saturday [7 Aug 2010] decided
to send some lawmakers under the coordination of CA member Sandhya Dev to
Banke following reports of gross negligence to control the disease. The DPH
office had confirmed the occurrence of cholera in some of the patients
undergoing treatment at various hospitals in the district on 3 Aug 2010.

At least 6 people have died and over 500 others have been affected in the
district due to the outbreak that spread in the district in the past 2 weeks.

--
