[3] Cholera, locally acquired - China (Hong Kong)
Date: Sat 7 Aug 2010
Source: Government of Hong Kong SAR Centre for Health Protection (CHP)
[edited]
<http://www.webnewswire.com/node/560107>


The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health is today
(7 Aug 2010) investigating a confirmed case of cholera and reminds people
to observe good personal, food, and environmental hygiene, whether in Hong
Kong or travelling abroad. The case involved a 66 year old woman who was a
food collateral of a cholera case (index case) confirmed on 5 Aug 2010. She
developed diarrhea on 2 Aug 2010.

Her symptoms subsided after one day without seeking medical attention. Her
stool specimen collected by CHP during the investigation of the index case
on 5 Aug 2010 grew _Vibrio cholerae_ today [7 Aug 2010]. CHP's
investigation revealed that the woman shared meals with the index case on 5
Aug 2010 in 4 food premises during the incubation period.

Both of them are now being treated in isolation at Princess Margaret
Hospital, and are in a stable condition. The woman did not have history of
recent travel. She lives in Sham Shiu Po and her home contacts have no
symptoms of cholera. Investigation continues and contacts of the patients
are under medical surveillance. This is the 5th case of cholera reported in
2010. There were 7 cholera cases in 2008, 3 cholera cases in 2007, 1 in
2006, and 5 in 2005.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

