[5] Cholera - Philippines (Zamboanga)
Date: Sun 18 Jul 2010
Source: Business Mirror [edited]
<http://businessmirror.com.ph/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=27810:cholera-dengue-outbreak-reported-in-zamboanga-city&catid=45:regions&Itemid=71>


The Zamboanga City Health Office here has declared an outbreak of cholera
in one of the barangays [sub districts]. Dr Rodel Agbulos, city health
officer, declared a cholera outbreak in barangay Vitali, 73 kilometres [45
miles] east of this city, citing the 30 cases reported as of Wed, 14 Jul 2010.

Agbulos said 17 of the 30 confirmed cases of cholera in sitio Tindalo,
barangay Vitali, remain at the Vitali Community Hospital. 1 fatality, a 3
year old child, was reported. He said patients complained of severe stomach
ache, vomiting, and loose bowel movements. The contaminated water from the
deep well, which is the only source of water in the area, was confirmed as
the root cause of the infection.

[byline: Bong Garcia jr]

