[6] Cholera - India (Maharashtra)
Date: Tue 27 Jul 2010
Source: DNA India [edited]
<http://www.dnaindia.com/health/report_cholera-like-epidemic-claims-one-in-ahmednagar-500-fall-sick_1415541>


A cholera-like epidemic is widely spreading in Bhingar and the adjoining
camp areas in Ahmednagar and about 500 people have fallen sick with it,
district civil hospital sources have said. Contaminated water supply and
lack of cleanliness are said to have caused the epidemic.

The epidemic has claimed one life at Boot hospital, a 52 year old man.
About 50 patients are being treated in the district civil hospital and a
special cell has been opened there. 30 patients are from Bhingar.

Many patients are getting treatment at Cantonment hospital and in private
hospitals. Cantonment hospital has a capacity of about 25 patients but
actually 35-40 patients are undergoing treatment.

--
