[7] Cholera - Viet Nam (Tay Ninh) ex Cambodia
Date: Tue 27 Jul 2010
Source: Viet Nam Ministry of Health [in Vietnamese, trans. & summ. Mod.QCN,
edited]
<http://moh.gov.vn/web/guest/vanbanthongthuong>


Tay Ninh Preventive Medicine Center reported that 3 acute diarrhea cases
have been hospitalized during 24 to 26 Jul 2010. Among those, 2 cases are
being treated in Go Dau District Health Station and one case is being
treated at Ben Cau District Health Station. 2 of those cases were confirmed
positive to _Vibrio cholerae_. All of these 3 cases were Cambodians who
were living in Svay Rieng. They came to Viet Nam for treatment after
getting the disease.

--
